  employment, are prohibited by a cooling-off period from taking up a
  specific occupational activity and who cannot find a suitable
  alternative occupational activity and are as a result unemployed are
  entitled to benefits for the duration of the prohibition and as long
  as they remain unemployed (ECB Conditions of Employment, page 18).
  - Unemployment allowance: 60% of the last basic salary for six
  months; 30% of the last basic salary for the subsequent six months
  and additional months in relation to years of service and age (ECB
  Conditions of Employment, page 17).  - Household and child
  allowances (ECB Conditions of Employment, page 17).  - Continued
  cover under the ECB health insurance, long-term care insurance, and
  accident insurance schemes, subject to payment of the relevant
  contributions (ECB Conditions of Employment, page 17).  - Education
  allowance in accordance with Article 19, up to EUR 393 per month, or
  up to EUR 764 per month for children with certified, imperative
  educational needs; payable only until the end of the academic year
  in which the member of staff becomes unemployed (ECB Conditions of
  Employment, page 17).  - One-off payment equivalent to one month’s
  salary at Band A, step 1 for each full year of service, subject to
  evidence of registration as unemployed and seeking employment with
  the competent employment authorities; not less than the equivalent
  of three months’ salary at Band A, step 1 and not more than the
  equivalent of twelve months’ salary at Band A, step 1 (ECB
  Conditions of Employment, page 18).  - Benefits of the same nature
  provided by other sources must be claimed and declared; such amounts
  are deducted from any amounts payable under this Article (ECB
  Conditions of Employment, page 18).
